1 T. Chopped garlic
1 C. Chopped onion
1 lb shrimp - thawed, deveined, no tail

SERVINGS: 9
MACROS: 16g C/19g F/ 6g P

Ingredients

•1 egg 
•6 tbsp maple syrup 
•1/4 cup melted coconut oil
•1/3 cup creamy almond butter
•1 tsp vanilla extract
•1 tbsp unsweetened almond milk
•1 cup almond flour 
•1/4 tsp baking soda
•1/2 tsp cinnamon
•3/4 dark chocolate bar 
•1/4 tsp sea salt

Instructions

Preheat oven to 325 degrees F.
Whisk egg* in large bowl then pour in maple syrup, melted coconut oil, almond butter, vanilla and almond milk to whisk again.

Stir in almond flour, baking soda, cinnamon and some of the sea salt. Fold in chocolate chunks.

Very lightly spray a cast iron skillet with oil then pour batter into the base and spread out evenly using a spatula. sprinkle sea salt, then place in the oven for 19 minutes on the center rack. 

ENJOY!

By including adequate protein in your meals, you can boost your metabolism and increase the number of calories burned throughout the day, facilitating fat loss and toning your tummy 🤩.

By including protein-rich foods in your meals and snacks, can experience improved appetite control and reduced cravings. This can prevent overeating and mindless snacking, contributing to a calorie deficit necessary for fat loss.
